    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for various articles, usually of silver or gold, intended for ecclesiastical use. Examples include patens, chalices, alms dishes, censers, or any other items that are made of or plated with silver or gold.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
